The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Rs 1.35 cr at stake during weekend 

 STAR RACER

 Calcutta: Poor fields notwithstanding, the RCTCs Invitational weekend, beginning from Saturday, is going to be well-attended. The turf club has made elaborate arrangements for the two-day racing bonanza and the racing is going to be a good fun; said an official. Equally confident was Cyrus Madan, steward, RCTC, who informed media persons on Thursday that sponsorship of a number of important races has made the clubs task easier. The total prize-money offered during the weekend is a shade under Rs 1.35 crore, thanks to the sponsors; said Madan.

 There are prizes galore, including a Chevrolet U-VA car, during the weekend. This years Hall Of Fame award goes to owner Deepak Khaitan.




